cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DC

The paper deals with formal methods and process calculi, which are typically studied in the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses encoding of mixed choice and process networks, which are topics that fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) respectively. The paper also presents a criterion to measure the degree of distribution in process networks, which is related to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
